# calculate the missing value of the attribute 
def calculateMissingItem(attributeListName):
    missing_value = 0
    for item in attributeListName:
        if item == '' or item == '[]' or item == '{}':
            missing_value += 1
    print("The attribute {} has {} missing value(s).".format(attributeListName.name, missing_value))

# get list removed missing values
def getRemovedMissingValueDataFrame(attributeListName):
    removed_missing_value_list = [x for x in attributeListName if x != '' and x != '[]' and x != '{}']
    ItemNo = [x+1 for x in range(len(removed_missing_value_list))]
    removed_missing_value_list = pd.DataFrame(removed_missing_value_list, index=ItemNo, columns=[attributeListName.name])
    removed_missing_value_list.name = attributeListName.name
    return removed_missing_value_list
In [10]:
def visualize_original_data_nominal(attributeListName):
    counter = Counter(attributeListName)
    attribute_top5 = counter.most_common(5)
    label_x = ['1', '2', '3', '4', '5']
    label_x_content = []
    label_y = []
    for i in range(5):
        label_x_content.append(attribute_top5[i][0])
        label_y.append(attribute_top5[i][1])
    attribute_plt = plt.bar(label_x, label_y, color='lightblue', tick_label=label_x)
    plt.xlabel("Attribute Item Name")
    plt.ylabel("Count Number")
    for a,b in zip(label_x, label_y):
        plt.text(a, b, b, ha='center', va='bottom')
    plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
    plt.title("Attribute " + attributeListName.name + " analysis")
    plt.savefig("cbg/"+attributeListName.name+"_origin.png")
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()
    print("The Content of the X axis:")
    for item in range(5):
        print("No.{}\t {}".format(item+1, label_x_content[item]))
In [ ]:
def visualize_original_data_numeric(attributeListName):
    attribute_name = attributeListName.name
    points_removed_missing_list = np.array(attributeListName[attribute_name]).astype(float).astype(int)
    points_sorted = np.sort(points_removed_missing_list)
    points_mean = np.mean(points_sorted)
    points_median = np.median(points_sorted)
    points_std = np.std(points_sorted)
    print("[Attribute points summary]\n Mean: {:.4f}\t Median: {:.4f}\t Std: {:.4f}".format(points_mean, points_median, points_std))
    points_cut_point = len(points_sorted)//4
    print("[Attribute points five-number summary]\n Min: {}\t Q1: {}\t Q2: {}\t Q3: {}\t Max: {}".format(points_sorted[0], points_sorted[points_cut_point], points_sorted[2*points_cut_point], points_sorted[3*points_cut_point], points_sorted[len(points_sorted)-1]))
    plt.boxplot(points_sorted, notch=False, vert=True)
    plt.xticks([1], [''])
    plt.xlabel(attributeListName.name)
    plt.title('Box plot')
    plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
    plt.title("Attribute " + attribute_name + " analysis")
    plt.savefig("cbg/"+ attribute_name +"_origin.png")
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()

def show_original_plot(attributeListName):
    attribute_name = attributeListName.name
    image_origin = mpimg.imread("cbg/"+ attribute_name +"_origin.png")
    print("Original data figure with missing values.")
    plt.clf()
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
    plt.imshow(image_origin)

def visualize_data_numeric(attributeListName):
    attribute_name = attributeListName.name
    points_list = np.array(attributeListName).astype(float).astype(int)
    points_sorted = np.sort(points_list)
    points_mean = np.mean(points_sorted)
    points_median = np.median(points_sorted)
    points_std = np.std(points_sorted)
    print("[Attribute points summary]\n Mean: {:.4f}\t Median: {:.4f}\t Std: {:.4f}".format(points_mean, points_median, points_std))
    points_cut_point = len(points_sorted)//4
    print("[Attribute points five-number summary]\n Min: {}\t Q1: {}\t Q2: {}\t Q3: {}\t Max: {}".format(points_sorted[0], points_sorted[points_cut_point], points_sorted[2*points_cut_point], points_sorted[3*points_cut_point], points_sorted[len(points_sorted)-1]))
    plt.boxplot(points_sorted, notch=False, vert=True)
    plt.xticks([1], [''])
    plt.xlabel(attributeListName.name)
    plt.title('Box plot')
    plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10.0, 4.0)
    plt.title("Attribute " + attribute_name + " analysis")
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()

def get_fill_in_with_the_most_present_value_list(attributeName):
    attribute_name = attributeName.name
    filled_count = 0
    filled_highest_value_list = attributeName.copy()
    attribute_counter = Counter(attributeName)
    attribute_top5 = attribute_counter.most_common(5)
    highest_value = attribute_top5[0][0]
    if highest_value == '' or highest_value == '[]' or highest_value == '{}':
        highest_value = attribute_top5[1][0]
    for item in range(1, len(filled_highest_value_list)+1):
        if filled_highest_value_list[item] == '' or filled_highest_value_list[item] == '[]' or filled_highest_value_list[item] == '{}':
            filled_highest_value_list[item] = highest_value
            filled_count += 1
    print("We filled {} item(s) by using the most present value {}.".format(filled_count, highest_value))
    return filled_highest_value_list
